5.8 percentage point positive impacts from accelerating pricing overcame the 5.2 percentage point negative impacts of
higher delivered product costs and investments in business. Acquisition adjusted fixed currency operating income
margins increased in 2021, as the positive impacts from higher volume and increased pricing more than offset the
negative impact of the comparison to lower variable compensation last year.
